modules.description: Provides functions to memoize and forgetfully memoize arbitrary functions, supporting both pure and side-effecting computations. Works with functions of any type, preserving type safety and allowing efficient caching of results. Enables optimization of repeated function calls in scenarios like recursive algorithms or expensive computations.

Provides functions for creating and managing a memoization cache, including lookup, insertion, and a custom reduction operation. It operates on functions with complex type signatures involving tuples and higher-order functions. Used to optimize repeated computations by storing and retrieving results based on input parameters.
